# IBEX Harness — Project Overview

## What this system is
IBEX Harness is a production-grade AI agent memory and context management platform. It proxies every LLM request, injects persistent memory and directive context, and provides behavioral drift detection for AI agents. Target users are enterprise engineering teams running AI agents at scale.

The quality bar is MAANG-level. This codebase must be readable by a principal engineer at Stripe who has never seen it before and they must be able to trust it.

## Service map

| Service | Language | Path | Purpose |
|---|---|---|---|
| Proxy | Go | `services/proxy/` | LLM request interception, <20ms overhead target |
| Auth | Go | `services/auth/` | Token validation, agent identity, gRPC |
| Memory | Python | `services/memory/` | Memory CRUD, vector search, dedup |
| Context Assembly | Python | `services/context/` | Context construction per request |
| Embedder | Python | `services/embedder/` | Text → vector embeddings |
| Worker | Python | `services/worker/` | Celery: extraction, fingerprinting, drift |
| API Server | Python | `services/api/` | Management REST API, dashboard backend |
| Dashboard | TypeScript/Next.js | `services/dashboard/` | Operator web UI |

